Title: Object: Typus Obedientiae
Description: In a rectangle at centre, Christ on the cross surrounded by ten scenes from his life all illustrating virtues: the Annunciation, the Nativity, the Circumcision, Last Supper, Mocking of Christ, the Flagellation, the Agony in the Garden, the Resurrection, the Flight into Egypt, and the Virgin by the Cross. Engraving
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (1722.I) (Wierix)
Mauquoy-Hendrickx 1979 / Les Estampes des Wierix ... catalogue raisonné (1454)
Alvin 1866 / Catalogue raisonné de l'oeuvre des trois frères Jan, Jérome et Antoine Wierix (1336)
